commit.message:
Fix clamp operator to work when output_min == output_max. (#65)

Summary:
Clamping should be ideally tightly bound to [output_min, output_min] or [output_max, output_max].
This fails in testing when zero_point is set to 255 which is possible when all values are negative.

Test Plan:
Unit tests

Prepare Qnnpack to build on Windows with MSVS (#58)

Sorry for the delay. :)

Support batch size 0 in all ops

While uncommon, operating on batch size 0 is perfectly valid.  (For
example, it can happen in Mask R-CNN if no proposals are detected.)

It looks like the name "convolution" was just copy-pasted.
